```

## Simulator
Always include this as the first import in every module script — required for the desktop simulator to work:
```js
import 'xrblocks/addons/simulator/SimulatorAddons.js';
```

## Architecture
- VRMAvatar.js — utility class: loads VRM via GLTFLoader + VRMLoaderPlugin, exposes vrm.scene, calls vrm.update(delta)
- VRMAvatarScript.js — xb.Script subclass: init() + update() lifecycle, owns scene setup, calls into VRMAvatar
- index.html — entry point
- Pattern mirrors demos/rain/ (RainScene.js + RainParticles.js)

## Key rules
- NEVER use xb.ModelViewer for VRM — VRMLoaderPlugin must be registered directly on the GLTFLoader instance before load
- NEVER use requestAnimationFrame manually — XRBlocks owns the render loop
- xb.Script lifecycle: init() for setup, update(time, frame) for per-frame logic
- Spring bones require vrm.update(delta) called every frame in update()
- Mixamo FBX retargeting via three-vrm's loadMixamoAnimation.js + mixamoVRMRigMap.js

## Demo behavior
- Third-person walking companion, follows user ~1.5m behind
- Idle animation when stationary, walk animation when moving
- Movement detected by diffing xb.user position each frame
- Smooth lerp for avatar position updates

## Reference demos in this repo
- demos/rain/ — primary structural pattern (multi-file Script + utility class)
- templates/0_basic/ — minimal xb.Script example
- samples/modelviewer/ — GLTFLoader usage reference
